{"id": "1462328040033095680", "channel_id": "1326453763355185215", "author_id": "229363452026552323", "author_name": "anikid9000", "content": "The yellow silk robed figure is a vague entity in Dreamquest Randolph Carter meets and quickly flees from, maybe inspired by the King in Yellow but also maybe not since its unclear when exactly Lovecraft actually read that story collection. The story itself seems to connect it to Nyarlathotep but of course the possible King in Yellow theming is something that can be easily fitted as well which Morimens may do. Anyway the similarity is the same mofit again personalized; yellow figure hiding their face, it is revealed to be some horrible visage. The \"form beyond naming\" Xu mentions here in her profile avatar you can buy could suggest Morimens has indeed conflated the King in Yellow and silk robed figure here along with Hastur, as He who Shall Not be Named and its variants is a common title under August Derleth.", "timestamp": "2026-01-18T06:09:33.485000+00:00", "reactions": [{"emoji": "happy", "emoji_id": "1356053849894420683", "count": 2}], "attachments": [{"id": "1462328039756140595", "filename": "image.png", "content_type": "image/webp", "size": 39374, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1326453763355185215/1462328039756140595/image.png?ex=6a34dd1d&is=6a338b9d&hm=2a2e489313a726b3a9493f8409ebe9f077a0fcba353719e477151598d96766f0&"}]}
